course_title: Women's Health Gender Related Nurse Practitioner Clinical Practicum II
class_notes: Online asynchronous and synchronous sessions. Face-to-face intensives dates: TBD
course_description: Students will develop sound diagnostic and management skills to care for pregnant and postpartum patients. Care of this population includes legal and ethical principles in decision making to improve health outcomes across diverse settings.
prerequisites: NRSG 594D prerequisite and NRSG 612D co-requisite or equivalent transfer credit. Students must enroll in NRSG 612D first.
